stylometry: Optimization is a way of finding the most efficient way of doing something. We did this by setting "Goal Seek" to minimize or maximize something within a problem. An example of optimizing is in the sailboat problem when we tried to maximize profit by ensuring that inventory and sales were done in the most effiicient way possible.Many linear programming models use optimization. Linear programming components include: Changing Cells-the cells that alter or change depending in a problem depending on results, Target Cells- cells we are trying to solve for, and Constraints-limitations in a problem that are restrictions.
